--- CompleteMazeBuilder Plug-in-Out Compliance & FPS Player - 2026-03-04
+++ Assets/Scripts/Core/06_Maze/CompleteMazeBuilder.cs

CHANGES FOR PLUG-IN-OUT COMPLIANCE:
===================================

1. HEADER DOCUMENTATION
   Added plug-in-out architecture notes:
   - CompleteMazeBuilder is a plug-in module for maze generation
   - Communicates with core systems via EventHandler
   - Independent but revolves around GameManager/EventHandler hub
   - Can be enabled/disabled without breaking core system

2. EVENTHANDLER INTEGRATION
   Added event handler reference and subscription:
   
   private EventHandler eventHandler;
   
   Awake():
   - Gets EventHandler.Instance (central hub)
   - Logs connection status
   
   OnEnable():
   - Subscribes to OnGameStateChanged event
   
   OnDisable():
   - Unsubscribes from OnGameStateChanged event
   
   OnGameStateChanged():
   - Handles game state changes via events (not direct GameManager access)

3. FPS PLAYER WITH CAMERA BETWEEN EYES
   PlacePlayerAtSpawn() now:
   - Creates proper FPS player with CharacterController
   - Adds PlayerController component (not just capsule)
   - PlayerController auto-positions camera at eye height (1.75m)
   - FPS movement enabled (WASD + mouse look + sprint + jump)
   
   Player Setup:
   ```csharp
   var playerGO = new GameObject("Player");
   playerGO.transform.position = new Vector3(cellSize * 1.5f, 1f, cellSize * 1.5f);
   
   // Add CharacterController (required for PlayerController)
   var controller = playerGO.AddComponent<CharacterController>();
   controller.radius = 0.4f;
   controller.height = 1.8f;
   controller.center = new Vector3(0f, 0.9f, 0f);
   
   // Add PlayerController (FPS movement + camera between eyes)
   player = playerGO.AddComponent<PlayerController>();
   ```

4. UNITY 6 COMPLIANCE
   - Uses FindFirstObjectByType (Unity 6 API)
   - New Input System (via PlayerController)
   - UTF-8 encoding, Unix LF line endings
   - Proper namespace: Code.Lavos.Core

